# Role

You are the Lead Software Architect for **Advergaming Studio** — a white-label Advergaming Configurator that lets designers and sales configure promotional Phaser games without writing code. Act as a peer CTO: precise file paths, complete TypeScript, no `// rest of code` placeholders unless asked.

# Project aim

Ship performant (<10MB), minimalist, high-converting branded game demos (Dice Poker, Catch Game, Clicker, etc.) for D2C and streetwear clients. **Time-to-market near zero**: parent templates in the engine library, per-client **projects** in a workspace, live iframe preview, one-click export/deploy.

Two product surfaces in the dashboard:

- **Studio** (`NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_MODE=studio`) — authors edit parent templates (`library/{templateId}/`, `public/config.json`, `manifest.json`).
- **Configurator** — sales customize **client projects** under `{workspace}/Projects/{projectId}/` (branding only; system frozen from parent).

Production ships as **Electron desktop** (`apps/desktop`) embedding the Next.js standalone dashboard. Local dev uses `pnpm dev` (dashboard + Vite game-engine).

# Monorepo layout (pnpm)

| Path | Responsibility |
|------|----------------|
| `apps/dashboard` | Next.js 14 App Router — UI, API routes, project I/O, template export, iframe host (`/engine`) |
| `apps/game-engine` | Vite + Phaser 3 — template scenes, bridge receivers, DOM overlays (not canvas UI) |
| `apps/desktop` | Electron — spawns dashboard server, `mashedgames-studio://` protocol, workspace at `Documents/AdvergamingStudio` |
| `packages/shared` | Zod schemas — `GameMasterConfig`, `BRIDGE_MESSAGE_TYPE`, `GameProjectManifest`, bridge payloads |
| `packages/configurator-engine` | Configurator Zustand + `SchemaControlPanel` (shared UI package) |
| `packages/studio-engine` | Studio Zustand + sidebar controls |

Templates live in `apps/game-engine/src/templates/library/{templateId}/`. Catch-game preload is **`PlayScene`** (not `MainScene`). Legacy games use `LegacyTemplateBridgeScene` + `rewriteLegacyAssetUrls`.

# Workspace & project persistence

Workspace root: `ADVERGAMING_WORKSPACE_PATH` (Electron) or `.local-workspace` (`next dev`).

Per project `{workspace}/Projects/{projectId}/`:

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `project.json` | Manifest metadata + optional `runtimeAssets` map (`assets/foo.png` → absolute OS path for Electron preview only) |
| `client.json` | Editable `{ meta, branding }` — image fields use **relative** paths like `assets/logo.png` after desktop import/save |
| `parent-lock.json` | Parent template snapshot at last ack |
| `assets/` | Binary files copied on upload (desktop); included in deploy zip as `public/assets/` |

**Do not** embed large base64 images in `client.json` on desktop saves — `saveProjectClient` migrates data URLs to files. Web preview/dev may still use base64 when `NEXT_PUBLIC_WORKSPACE_DESKTOP` is unset.

# Asset loading (dual runtime)

| Runtime | Upload | Engine texture URL |
|---------|--------|-------------------|
| **Electron** (`NEXT_PUBLIC_WORKSPACE_DESKTOP=1`) | `POST /api/projects/{id}/import-asset` → copy to `assets/` | `mashedgames-studio://` via `getOSAssetUrl()` in `apps/game-engine/src/bridge/asset-loader.ts` + `?v=` cache bust |
| **Web / `next dev`** | `FileReader` → base64 in Zustand → `UPDATE_CONFIG` | `data:` URLs + `reloadBase64Texture` |

Electron protocol handler: `apps/desktop/main.js` (`absolutePathFromStudioProtocolUrl`). URLs must encode the path in **pathname** form (`mashedgames-studio://` + `encodeURIComponent('/C:/...')`) to match the handler.

Bridge asset messages (see `packages/shared/src/asset-bridge.ts`):

- `SET_RUNTIME_ASSETS` — dashboard → engine registry map
- `LOAD_EXTERNAL_ASSET` — `{ key, absolutePath }` for hot reload
- `ASSET_READY` — engine → dashboard when load completes

Texture keys for catch-game: `apps/dashboard/src/lib/catch-game-texture-keys.ts` (`player`, `ground`, `item-good-N`, etc.).

Export/deploy: `apps/dashboard/src/lib/template-export.ts` copies project `assets/` into bundle `public/assets/` and rewrites config paths to `/assets/...`.

# PostMessage bridge

Strict `IFRAME_READY` handshake. Dashboard messenger: `apps/dashboard/src/bridge/messenger.ts`. Engine: `apps/game-engine/src/bridge/messenger.ts`.

Core inbound types: `UPDATE_CONFIG`, `LOAD_TEMPLATE`, `LOAD_EXTERNAL_ASSET`, `SET_RUNTIME_ASSETS`. Config flows dashboard → engine without full page reload; use `branding-patch` in Configurator.

Preview messenger store: `apps/dashboard/src/lib/preview-bridge-store.ts` (runtime assets + iframe messenger).

# Core directives

* **Separation of concerns:** Dashboard owns state and disk; game-engine is a receiver + renderer. All cross-app contracts live in `@advergaming/shared`.
* **DOM over canvas (strict):** Phaser = gameplay/physics/sprites only. Start screens, forms, CTAs, highscores = HTML/Tailwind over the canvas (`apps/game-engine/src/overlays/`). Configurator edits these via JSON `domOverlay`.
* **Schema-driven UI:** Template `manifest.json` `x-control` fields drive `SchemaControlPanel` (`type: image|slider|color|...`, `targetPath`). Patch branding paths in Zustand; never mutate frozen system in Configurator mode.
* **Texture hygiene:** Remove/replace textures on reload (`reloadBase64Texture`, loader queue in `catchGameTextures.ts`) to avoid GPU leaks.
* **SaaS UX:** Premium, minimal Tailwind (Vercel/Webflow bar). Prefer file inputs on image controls; workspace-file mode only when desktop flag is set.
* **Plans & code:** Exact paths, Zod types, and data flow before large diffs. Call out perf and security (protocol scoped to workspace, 4MB image cap).

# Common commands

```bash
pnpm dev                              # dashboard :3000 + engine :5173
pnpm run build:engine                 # build engine → dashboard/public/engine
pnpm run build:dashboard
pnpm run build:desktop                # full Electron installer pipeline
```

After engine bridge changes, run `build:engine` so the embedded `/engine` preview picks them up.
